   <text>
      <body>
         <div>
            <pb facs="#facs_1" n="1" xml:id="img_0001"/>
            <pb facs="#facs_2" n="2" xml:id="img_0002"/>
            <ab facs="#facs_2_tr_1">
               <lb facs="#facs_2_tr_1_tl_3" n="N001"/><hi style="text-decoration: underline;">Religion and Culture</hi> (possible outline I)
               <lb facs="#facs_2_tr_1_tl_5" n="N002"/><hi style="text-decoration: underline;">First Lecture: The processes of <Life>life </Life>and the functions</hi>
               <lb facs="#facs_2_tr_1_tl_6" n="N003"/><hi style="text-decoration: underline;">of the <Spirit>spirit.</Spirit></hi>
               <lb facs="#facs_2_tr_1_tl_7" n="N004"/>Intr. The method of progressive elimination.
               <lb facs="#facs_2_tr_1_tl_8" n="N005"/><hi style="text-decoration: underline;">I. The dynamics of life and its processes.</hi>
               <lb facs="#facs_2_tr_1_tl_9" n="N006"/>1. Selfidentity and selfalteration and the danger
               <lb facs="#facs_2_tr_1_tl_10" n="N007"/>of life.
               <lb facs="#facs_2_tr_1_tl_11" n="N008"/>2. The process of selfintegration and the centered-
               <lb facs="#facs_2_tr_1_tl_12" n="N009"/>ness of life.
               <lb facs="#facs_2_tr_1_tl_13" n="N010"/>3. The process of selfcreation and the growth of
               <lb facs="#facs_2_tr_1_tl_14" n="N011"/>life.
               <lb facs="#facs_2_tr_1_tl_15" n="N012"/>4. The process of selftranscendence and the sublime-
               <lb facs="#facs_2_tr_1_tl_16" n="N013"/>ness of life.
            </ab>
            <pb facs="#facs_3" n="3" xml:id="img_0003"/>
            <ab facs="#facs_3_tr_1">
               <lb facs="#facs_3_tr_1_tl_1" n="N001"/><hi style="text-decoration: underline;">II. The <Spirit>spirit</Spirit> of man and its three main func-</hi>
               <lb facs="#facs_3_tr_1_tl_2" n="N002"/><hi style="text-decoration: underline;">tions.</hi>
               <lb facs="#facs_3_tr_1_tl_3" n="N003"/>1. The function of spiritual selfintegration or <Morality>mo-
               <lb break="no" facs="#facs_3_tr_1_tl_4" n="N004"/>rality</Morality>
               <lb facs="#facs_3_tr_1_tl_5" n="N005"/>2. The function of spiritual selfcreation or <Culture>cul-
               <lb break="no" facs="#facs_3_tr_1_tl_6" n="N006"/>ture.</Culture>
               <lb facs="#facs_3_tr_1_tl_7" n="N007"/>3. The function of spiritual selftranscendence or
               <lb facs="#facs_3_tr_1_tl_8" n="N008"/><Religion>religion</Religion>.
               <lb facs="#facs_3_tr_1_tl_9" n="N009"/><hi style="text-decoration: underline;">III. The mutual within-each-otherness of the three</hi>
               <lb facs="#facs_3_tr_1_tl_10" n="N010"/><hi style="text-decoration: underline;">functions.</hi>
               <lb facs="#facs_3_tr_1_tl_11" n="N011"/><hi style="text-decoration: underline;">IV. The possible tensions and real conflicts</hi>
               <lb facs="#facs_3_tr_1_tl_12" n="N012"/><hi style="text-decoration: underline;">between the three functions.</hi>
            </ab>
         </div>
      </body>
   </text>
